-- Indian shares slump; head towards biggest single-day fall in 10 months
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Tue Jul 08, 2014 05:56AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, July 8 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell more than 2 percent on Tuesday, heading towards their biggest single-day fall in over 10 months as a  lower-than-expected railway budget outlay sparked worries about subdued government expenditure in the federal budget due on Thursday.

Among blue-chips, Larsen & Toubro <LART.NS> fell 4.5 percent while Reliance Industries <RELI.NS> lost 3.3 percent.